 <h2 id="emacs-293-emergency-release"> <span class="timestamp-wrapper"> <span class="timestamp">25 March 2024</span></span> Emacs 29.3 emergency release</h2>
 <div class="outline-text-2" id="text-emacs-293-emergency-release">
 <p>
It was only last week when I upgraded to Emacs 29.2. Yup, I was late to the party. This week, we have a new release.
</p>

 <p>
Emacs 29.3 is an  <a href="https://lists.gnu.org/archive/html/emacs-devel/2024-03/msg00611.html">emergency bugfix release</a>, so this time I've upgraded promptly. I'm on macOS using the great  <a href="https://github.com/d12frosted/homebrew-emacs-plus">Emacs Plus</a> so upgraded via  <a href="https://brew.sh/">Homebrew</a> using:
</p>

 <div class="org-src-container">
 <pre class="src src-sh">brew reinstall emacs-plus@29 --with-imagemagick --with-no-frame-refocus --with-native-comp --with-savchenkovaleriy-big-sur-3d-icon --with-poll
</pre>
</div>


 <div class="figure" id="org4f65fa1">
 <p> <img alt="29.3.png" src="https://xenodium.com/images/emacs-293-emergency-release/29.3.png" width="60%" /></p>
</div>

 <p>
ps. Like this splash screen? Check out the  <a href="https://xenodium.com/my-emacs-eye-candy/">Emacs eye candy post</a>.
</p>
